{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64b16a95f23ac7d519f9b5bf", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76cfc52ffa3c944600e0"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "632c83573e3fd59bda92e46c", "title": "JEE Advanced 2022 (Paper 1)", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "multipleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 240, "question": {"text": "<p>Three plane mirrors form an equilateral triangle with each side of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>. There is a small hole at a distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;from one of the corners as shown in the figure. A ray of light is passed through the hole at an angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&theta;</mi></math> and can only come out through the same hole. The cross section of the mirror configuration and the ray of light lie on the same plane.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/dfb4b404-b280-422d-bb27-60fc100081eb-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 157px;\" /></p><p>Which of the following statement(s) is(are) correct?</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "F9xpw", "text": "The ray of light will come out for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>L</mi></math>.", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "sBF9N", "text": "There is an angle for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> at which the ray of light will come out after two reflections.", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "Uw5Ku", "text": "The ray of light will NEVER come out for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>.", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "iMX7N", "text": "The ray of light will come out for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> after six reflections.", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/61b31243-8ee3-4538-8fe1-ae2a469b14d7-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 169px;\" /></p><p>As we can see, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, the ray will incident normally and hence will retrace its path, hence the ray will come out for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>L</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mi>A</mi></mfenced></math> is correct</p><p>Considering the symmetry of the situation, we can have:</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/f7d580ea-927c-45b0-8746-b3eb83f9aa5a-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 179px;\" /></p><p>Thus, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, ray will come out from the setup&nbsp;after two reflections.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mi>B</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is correct</p><p>Now, when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>, the ray on entering the setup will suffer five reflections and eventually will come out.</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/3296ba29-066c-43f7-a213-028c6ed0f832-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 225px;\" /></p><p>As is clear from the above diagram, ray comes out.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mi>C</mi></mfenced></math> is not correct</p><p>Also, as is clear from the above diagram, total number of reflections <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mi>D</mi></mfenced></math> is not correct.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "70825899fcf5415c8fcbb7542fc4a433", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/p7NcBL4zd6rnf.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/p7NcBL4zd6rnf.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "64c7e8e829737784b294e469", "isFree": false}, {"premiumModuleId": "6788cc0b2dbc1ecacabb7026", "isFree": false}], "description": "JEE Advanced (All PYQs from 2023 - 2013)"}, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "questionLabels": [], "__v": 0, "masterId": "MOGJAPYQ85575961", "bucket": "", "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperT